last time we did gruul, i had to tank (mage who normaly does it wasn't
there)

like, NO PRESSURE !
lol

use invisibility to go up to the ledge on the right
stand on the corner and shoot the mage, we have the mage pulling to start,
hunters doing misdirect to grab the other mobs etc
do detect magic, fire shield, shoot the crap out of him to start the fight,
he runs up to right in front of me, steal shield off him
drop down, the mage stays up on the ledge, which is great, since his AOE
does 4-5k damage, which isn't much help ...

anyway, the buff lasts 30 seconds, it runs out, and you have to grab the
next one right away, if you take 2 fireballs(9k damage), you die, and it's a
wipe (near end of buff, stop dps and just spam spellsteal button)

gear wise just get the mages to go AH and buy some stamina greens
they need to have about 12k stam when buffed(10k unbuffed), more is better
of course ( you gotta be able to take a 9k fireball, and have 2k health or
so to soak up the next fireball, which will be nerfed due to you having
shield)

don't forget to have enough mana, it's not *too* important though, you only
need enough to spellsteal and dps long enough for the raid to come over and
kill the mage
some +dmg is nice (makes more threat)

you also need as much +hit you can pack in
if you get a resist when using spellsteal, you are prob screwed

don't go overboard and buy a complete 'of stamina' set, neither get every
+hit item you can find, you just need to balance it really
i ended up using about errrmm, maybe half my items as stamina greens, get
stam enchants and stuff too
i had about 12k health, 8.5k mana, 5% hit, 600+damage

anyone, was fun tanking, i screwed up the first time though, the stupid
shammy endedup near me, so i moved to get out the way of the AOE, and the
buff ran out doh, second time boss down, no problem :)
