as said in other responses, the mage needs stamina and hit (balanced)

we assign two tanks (warrior or feral) to the warlock and have two warlocks
banish the pets.
also we assign 2 healers for their aid.

mage is healed by one healer
and the two hunters tanking the shaman are healed by another healer.
the rest concentrates on the mt.

shaman and mt healer may drop a hot or so to the one tanking the healer.

after that the warlock dies, then we split dps
ranged take down the mage and rogues offwarriors and feral druids take down
the shaman.

once that is done you only have maulgar to deal with.

during the fight assign any free tank to assist in keeping the warlock pets
away from the healers until banished.

i think your very near to a kill since the fight is hard in the beginning
and gets easier the more adds you take down.
similar to fathom lord karathress (only difference is karathress inherits
abilities from his adds, maulgar doesnt)

gruul is simply coordination and dps ;)

have fun !
